name: connective tissue benign neoplasm
definition: A musculoskeletal system benign neoplasm that is located_in connective tissue. [url:http\://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Connective_tissue_neoplasm]

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a Phase I trial, two desmoid tumor patients demonstrated stable disease for greater than 6 months when treated with Ipafricept (OMP-54F28) (PMID: 28954784).

references.title: A First-in-Human Phase I Study of the Anticancer Stem Cell Agent Ipafricept (OMP-54F28), a Decoy Receptor for Wnt Ligands, in Patients with Advanced Solid Tumors.
